casebody.data:
FISS et al., Respondents, v. WARREN, Appellant. (Common Pleas of New York City and County, General Term. January 4, 1894.) Appeal from city court, general term. Action by William Piss .and John P. Dorr against Henry M. Warren.

Argued before BOOKSTAVER, BISCHOFF, and PRYOR, JJ.

Strong, Hermon & Matthewson, for appellant. E. B. La Fetra, for respondents.

No opinion. Judgment affirmed, with costs. See 26 N. Y. Supp. 75.
